da13f9db-a1da-416e-8157-48cf149009e7.text:
Let $a, b \in \Z$ such that the geometric mean is an integer.
Then $a$ and $b$ are similar plane numbers.
{{EuclidPropStatement|book=VIII|prop=20|body=If one mean proportional number fall between two numbers, the numbers will be similar plane numbers.}}

821e54e2-1a3f-4023-b41f-1a415ee398f9.text:
Let $\struct{R, 
orm {\,\cdot\,} }$ be a normed division ring.
Let $a \in R$.
Let $\epsilon \in \R_{>0}$ be a strictly positive real number.
Let $\map {{B_\epsilon}^-} {a; 
orm {\,\cdot\,} }$ denote the $\epsilon$-closed ball of $a$ in $\struct {R, 
orm {\,\cdot\,} }$.
Let $\map {B_\epsilon} {a; 
orm {\,\cdot\,} }$ denote the $\epsilon$-open ball of $a$ in $\struct {R, 
orm {\,\cdot\,} }$.
Let $\map {S_\epsilon} {a; 
orm {\,\cdot\,} }$ denote the $\epsilon$-sphere of $a$ in $\struct {R, 
